name: Making of Modern Law: Foreign Primary Sources, 1600-1970
description: Foreign Primary Sources, 1600-1970 complements the collection of treatises found in Foreign, Comparative and International Law 1600-1926. Importantly, it provides an interpretive analysis with books on codes, the “primary sources” of law. This archive will operate as the first of two parts, with the second part covering southern Europe, Latin America, and jurisdictions outside Europe.
